 Why? Because you are now, according to the scriptures, through faith you are in Christ.

475
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:40,000
 Which is amazing news.

476
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:44,000
 So I tell you this just to say the cross must always be bigger than your failure.

477
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:47,000
 Always.

478
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:52,000
 Now, if you've wronged someone, go seek forgiveness.

479
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:55,000
 Go make it right.

480
00:31:55,000 --> 00:32:00,000
 And I'll tell you this, like you don't have to forget about your past.

481
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:03,000
 You just have to put your past in the right place.

482
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:08,000
 Your past no longer has the right to remind you of what you've done.

483
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:12,000
 It only has the right to remind you of what Jesus has done.

484
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:23,000
 Your past failure's only responsibility now is to display the beauty and the greatness of God's grace.

485
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:29,000
 The third thing that I want you to know is this, your life can still glorify Jesus.

486
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:31,000
 That's amazing news.

487
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:34,000
 Your life can still glorify Jesus.

488
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:43,000
 Look at what it tells us about Peter, verses 18 and 19.

489
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:46,000
 So Jesus has just said three different times, "Do you love me?"

490
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:50,000
 Peter says, "Yes." He's like, "Feed my sheep. Tend my lambs."

491
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:52,000
 Do you know what he's telling him?

492
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:58,000
 He's saying, "Peter, go play a significant role in the building of my church."

493
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:00,000
 Not a building, but a people.

494
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:03,000
 So you fast forward to the book of Acts, and you know what you see?

495
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:06,000
 You see Peter is the leader.

496
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:10,000
 Like, he's the one who stands up, and when he gives a sermon like I'm doing right now,

497
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:14,000
 3,000 people trust Christ just like that.

498
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:20,000
 So what Jesus is saying when he says, "Hey, go feed my sheep," he's saying, "Go, go lead.

499
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:22,000
 Go do something for my glory."

500
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:26,000
 Now watch what he says in verse 18.

501
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:29,000
 Jesus says, "Truly, truly, I say to you, when you were young,

502
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:32,000
 you used to dress yourself and walk wherever you wanted.

503
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:35,000
 But when you are old, you will stretch out your hands,

504
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:39,000
 and another will dress you and carry you where you do not want to go."

505
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:41,000
 Verse 19, don't miss it.

506
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:48,000
 "This he said to show by what kind of death he was to glorify God.

507
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:53,000
 And after saying this, he said to them, 'Follow me.'"

508
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:55,000
 Do you know what this is a reference to?

509
00:33:55,000 --> 00:34:00,000
 Jesus right here is referring to the death Peter was going to die.

510
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:03,000
 Peter was going to die by crucifixion.

511
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:07,000
 Tradition tells us that he was even crucified upside down.

512
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:09,000
 But I want you to see the wording.

513
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:13,000
 This is Jesus himself saying, "Look, right now I'm just talking about the death

514
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:17,000
 that you are going to die to glorify me."

515
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:24,000
 Jesus himself is saying, "It is still possible for you, Peter, to glorify me."

516
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:28,000
 And you know what's amazing is when you do go and read the book of Acts,

517
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:34,000
 you know what the story of Peter's life becomes?

518
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:37,000
 Peter's story isn't, "I failed."

519
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:42,000
 Peter's story was, he was imperfect but faithful.

520
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:46,000
 Like he went out and he led for Jesus, and yet he still sinned.

521
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:48,000
 He still struggled.

522
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:52,000
 Like there's a story where Paul has to call Peter out.

523
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:55,000
 But the label of his life was not failure.

524
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:58,000
 It was imperfect but faithful.

525
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:00,000
 And I'll just tell you this.

526
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:03,000
 Like I've got a wife and three kids.

527
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:12,000
 And when I die at my funeral, the greatest thing that anyone could say about me

528
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:16,000
 is for my wife or my kids or my friends to stand up and say,

529
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:19,000
 "You know what, Timothy Atik, he was an imperfect person.

530
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:21,000
 He was very imperfect."

531
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:25,000
 I want my wife to stand up there and say, "You know what, he was too moody sometimes.

532
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:29,000
 He was imperfect, but he was faithful.

533
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:32,000
 He was faithful to follow Jesus.

534
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:34,000
 He was faithful to love his spouse.

535
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:36,000
 He was faithful to love his kids.

536
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:39,000
 He was faithful to love God's church.

537
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:42,000
 He was imperfect but faithful."

538
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:46,000
 There's nothing--there's not a bigger compliment that I could receive

539
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:48,000
 or that you could receive.

540
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:52,000
 I'd just tell you this to say your life can still glorify Jesus.

541
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:57,000
 Don't let your limited perspective tell you what a limitless God can and can't do

542
00:35:57,000 --> 00:36:00,000
 in and through you.

543
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:02,000
 You can still glorify God in dating.

544
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:04,000
 You can still glorify God in marriage.

545
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:05,000
 You can still glorify God as a parent.

546
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:07,000
 You can still glorify God as a co-worker.

547
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:11,000
 You can still glorify God as a boss or an employee.

548
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:13,000
 I don't say this to minimize our sin.

549
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:18,000
 I just say it to maximize the power of God's grace.

550
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:19,000
 And so you know what?

551
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:22,000
 Like you've heard me--if you've been at the porch for a while,

552
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:28,000
 you've heard me share about my story of how I lived a compromising life

553
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:34,000
 and I was working at a church and I had to step off of staff.

554
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:38,000
 For the new people in the room, do you know what church that was?

555
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:41,000
 Watermark Community Church.

556
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:45,000
 It was this church that I had to sit with a room full of 50 to 60 staff

557
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:48,000
 and just tell them about my sin.

558
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:52,000
 It was at this church that I was asked to leave staff

559
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:57,000
 and to step out of leadership for a period of time because of my sin.

560
00:36:57,000 --> 00:37:02,000
 And now God in his kindness and in his grace has brought me back.

561
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:05,000
 Why? Because he wasn't done with me.

562
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:08,000
 And so the reason I share my story is that I don't have a story to hide.

563
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:11,000
 I have a story to tell.

564
00:37:11,000 --> 00:37:17,000
 Because my story now, it's a trophy of God's grace.

565
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:20,000
 And I've told my story now to tens of thousands of people.

566
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:23,000
 I've gotten to sit one-on-one with young adults

567
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:27,000
 and talk to them about my failures during that season.

568
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:30,000
 And I don't have to do it with shame in my heart.

569
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:34,000
 I do it free of shame.

570
00:37:34,000 --> 00:37:39,000
 Because now my past's only responsibility

571
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:44,000
 is to remind me of just how great God's grace has been in my life.

572
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:49,000
 It is a trophy of God's grace that I can stand up here tonight

573
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:54,000
 and say, "I don't have a story to hide. You can know my past."

574
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:57,000
 Because Jesus has restored me from my past.

575
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:59,000
 He has redeemed me from it.

576
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:06,000
 And the cross of Jesus Christ is capable to deal with all of our sin.

577
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:08,000
 I hope you believe that tonight.

578
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:13,000
 [applause]

579
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:22,000
 So I just want to close by talking about how you respond to a message like this.

580
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:25,000
 Here it is.

581
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:29,000
 Peter ran to Jesus instead of running from Jesus.

582
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:32,000
 You know what I love about Peter is that he denied Jesus three times,

583
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:35,000
 and then when John looks at him and they're on the boat,

584
00:38:35,000 --> 00:38:37,000
 and he's like, "Hey, that's Jesus."

585
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:39,000
 You know what Jesus--Peter does?

586
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:42,000
 He flings himself into the water and just is like,

587
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:45,000
 "I don't have time to wait for us to paddle there.

588
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:48,000
 I want to get to Jesus now."

589
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:52,000
 Instead of running from him, he ran to him.

590
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:56,000
 And here's what I love. When Peter came to Jesus,

591
00:38:56,000 --> 00:39:02,000
 what was the question that Jesus asked Peter?

592
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:06,000
 "Do you promise you're never going to deny me again?"

593
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:08,000
 It wasn't that question.

594
00:39:08,000 --> 00:39:12,000
 Now, Peter, you're committed to going to church every week from here on out, right?

595
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:14,000
 That's part of the deal.

596
00:39:14,000 --> 00:39:17,000
 It wasn't that question either.

597
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:21,000
 Peter, you're not going to embarrass me and screw up again, right?

598
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:24,000
 Not that question either.

599
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:26,000
 What was the question?

600
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:29,000
 "Do you love me?"

601
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:32,000
 That's the question on the table for you tonight.

602
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:35,000
 It's not, "Do you promise?"

603
00:39:35,000 --> 00:39:40,000
 It's not, "Can you find someone that screwed up worse than you?"

604
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:48,000
 It's not, "How are you going to punish yourself to make things right?"

605
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:50,000
 It's, "Do you love me?"

606
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:52,000
 So here's the deal.

607
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:55,000
 If you're here tonight and you don't have a relationship with Jesus Christ,

608
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:58,000
 you are not a Christian.

609
00:39:58,000 --> 00:40:05,000
 If that's you, I just want you to know that when we talk about knowing Jesus,

610
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:10,000
 what we're talking about is we're talking about knowing the one

611
00:40:10,000 --> 00:40:15,000
 who left heaven and came to earth and lived a perfect life

612
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:18,000
 because we have lived very imperfect lives,

613
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:23,000
 and he died the death that we all deserved to die for our sin.

614
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:28,000
 But when he died, what he was doing, he was taking all of the punishment

615
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:31,000
 that our failures deserved.

616
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:35,000
 And then we believe that this Jesus, he walked out of the grave

617
00:40:35,000 --> 00:40:39,000
 as a demonstration that he was victorious over all of our failures.

618
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:42,000
 So tonight, his victory can be your victory.

619
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:46,000
 Your life does not have to be defined by your failures.

620
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:51,000
 It can be defined by his forgiveness and his favor towards you.

621
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:55,000
 But it's only possible through faith.

622
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:59,000
 It's only possible by you coming to a place where you talk to God

623
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:03,000
 and you say, "Jesus, everything he's talking about, I want that to be true for me.

624
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:05,000
 God, I give my life to you.

625
00:41:05,000 --> 00:41:07,000
 You can be in charge of my life.

626
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:09,000
 Would you just come in? Would you be my Savior?

627
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:13,000
 Would you be my King? Would you rule in my life?

628
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:17,000
 I give my life to you. If that is possible, if it's possible

629
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:23,000
 for you to not just forgive me, but to give me the righteousness of Christ.

630
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:25,000
 God, I want that.

631
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:29,000
 If that's you, would you come to him tonight?

632
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:33,000
 If you're here and you are a Christian, but you're running from Jesus right now

633
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:36,000
 because you're running in your shame,

634
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:40,000
 you're living under the banner of failure,

635
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:44,000
 stop running. Stop running.

636
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:48,000
 God in his love for you has brought you here

637
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:52,000
 so that he could just ask you this question, "Do you love me?"

638
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:58,000
 All you have to do is say, "I do love you, God. Forgive me."

639
00:41:58,000 --> 00:42:02,000
 And then you know what? If you've sought God for forgiveness

640
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:07,000
 and yet you're still living in shame, let me just tell you what needs to happen.

641
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:11,000
 You need to begin to agree with God about your sin.

642
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:16,000
 Because Jesus is saying tonight, "I canceled the record."

643
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:20,000
 And yet when we let shame rule, you know what we're saying back to God?

644
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:22,000
 We're saying, "Yeah, but what about my record?"

645
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:27,000
 He's like, "I canceled it." It's like, "Yeah, but what about that sin on the record?"

646
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:33,000
 He's like, "Yeah, I took it away." "Yeah, but I don't know about that sin."

647
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:39,000
 We have to agree with him. You canceled the record.

648
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:43,000
 Because you, Jesus, are greater than my sin, and I trust you.

649
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:46,000
 So would you come to him tonight?

650
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:50,000
 Whatever it is, would you run towards Jesus,

651
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:54,000
 and would you experience his grace and his forgiveness?

652
00:42:54,000 --> 00:42:58,000
 Would you allow him to trade your story of failure

653
00:42:58,000 --> 00:43:01,000
 for his story of forgiveness and favor?

654
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:03,000
 Let's pray together.

655
00:43:03,000 --> 00:43:12,000
 I just want to ask, if you're here tonight, and you're not a Christian,

656
00:43:12,000 --> 00:43:15,000
 but everything I said just a minute ago makes sense,

657
00:43:15,000 --> 00:43:19,000
 and you're sitting there saying, "Yes, I want to begin a relationship with Jesus Christ tonight.

658
00:43:19,000 --> 00:43:21,000
 I want everything that you just said to be true to me."

659
00:43:21,000 --> 00:43:25,000
 If that's you, with eyes closed, would you slip up your hand real quick,

660
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:28,000
 just so I know who I'm talking to in this place tonight?

661
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:33,000
 Great. Awesome.

662
00:43:33,000 --> 00:43:37,000
 Then if that's you, I just encourage you right now to pray and say,

663
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,000
 "Lord Jesus, I want everything he just said.

664
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:45,000
 Would you come into my life?

665
00:43:45,000 --> 00:43:50,000
 Would you forgive me of all of my sins?"

666
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:56,000
 Just tell him, "Thank you." Say, "Thank you, Jesus, that you died for me.

667
00:43:57,000 --> 00:44:00,000
 Thank you that you rose from the dead for me.

668
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:04,000
 Would you save me?

669
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:08,000
 And would you lead me in a new life?"

670
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:16,000
 And then if you're here tonight, and you are a believer that's just been walking in shame,

671
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:20,000
 like we sang a song earlier,

672
00:44:20,000 --> 00:44:24,000
 talking about witnessing the faithfulness of God,

673
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:27,000
 and telling of his faithfulness, that's what I've done tonight,

674
00:44:27,000 --> 00:44:29,000
 is I've stood up here and I've told you,

675
00:44:29,000 --> 00:44:33,000
 I've witnessed the faithfulness of God in my own life to restore me from my sin,

676
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:35,000
 and so I've testified about it to you.

677
00:44:35,000 --> 00:44:38,000
 And I want that for you.

678
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:42,000
 So maybe you just sit there and you thank God for his faithfulness

679
00:44:42,000 --> 00:44:45,000
 to cancel the record of your sins.

680
00:44:45,000 --> 00:44:51,000
 And then maybe you stand and you sing and you testify of his goodness

681
00:44:51,000 --> 00:44:53,000
 and his faithfulness in your life,

682
00:44:53,000 --> 00:44:55,000
 but don't just run out of here.

683
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:57,000
 Do business with the Lord now.

684
00:44:57,000 --> 00:45:00,000
 God, you are good.

685
00:45:00,000 --> 00:45:04,000
 Thank you for your kindness in our lives.

686
00:45:04,000 --> 00:45:06,000
 That you don't give up on us.

687
00:45:06,000 --> 00:45:09,000
 That you're not even close to giving up on us.

688
00:45:09,000 --> 00:45:10,000
 You still love us.

689
00:45:10,000 --> 00:45:12,000
 You still pursue us.

690
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:16,000
 I pray for people who carried shame in,

691
00:45:16,000 --> 00:45:19,000
 may they not carry it back out.

692
00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:22,000
 May they leave it here

693
00:45:22,000 --> 00:45:24,000
 and leave free.

694
00:45:24,000 --> 00:45:26,000
 We need you. We love you.

695
00:45:26,000 --> 00:45:28,000
 Amen.

